{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h1>Lorem Ipsum</h1>\n<p><strong><em>January 14th, 2019</em> by Ratnasambhav Priyadarshi</strong></p>\n<h2>Subtitle</h2>\n<p><a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/27c25ef3c9ed146709cc3db177567465/155f9/1.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; max-width: 100vw; width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; min-height: 300px; position: relative max-width: 650px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 59.77777777777777%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"image\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/27c25ef3c9ed146709cc3db177567465/bc0fb/1.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/27c25ef3c9ed146709cc3db177567465/48864/1.jpg 163w,\n/static/27c25ef3c9ed146709cc3db177567465/734c4/1.jpg 325w,\n/static/27c25ef3c9ed146709cc3db177567465/bc0fb/1.jpg 650w,\n/static/27c25ef3c9ed146709cc3db177567465/7c49c/1.jpg 975w,\n/static/27c25ef3c9ed146709cc3db177567465/31d1e/1.jpg 1300w,\n/static/27c25ef3c9ed146709cc3db177567465/155f9/1.jpg 1800w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\"\n      />\n  </span>\n  </a></p>\n<p>The <code>gatsby-source-filesystem</code> plugin we configured earlier expects our content to be in <code>src/pages</code>, so that’s exactly where we’ll put it!</p>\n<p>Gatsby is not at all prescriptive in naming conventions, but a typical practice for blog posts is to name the folder something like <code>MM-DD-YYYY-title</code>, e.g. <code>07-12-2017-hello-worl</code>d. Let’s do just that, and create the folder <code>src/pages/07-12-2017-getting-started</code>, and place an <code>index.md</code> inside!</p>\n<p>The content of this Markdown file will be our blog post, authored in Markdown (of course!). Here’s what it’ll look like:</p>\n<pre><code>---\npath: \"/hello-world\"\ndate: \"2017-07-12T17:12:33.962Z\"\ntitle: \"My First Gatsby Post\"\n---\n\nOooooh-weeee, my first blog post!\n</code></pre>","frontmatter":{"date":"January 13, 2019","path":"/blog/hello-world","title":"Lorem Ipsum"}}},"pageContext":{}}